parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls while accelerating
the "do not turn off the vehicle until arriving at destination" warning message is illuminated
the vehicle goes into limp mode and will not accelerate above 20 MPH.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can cause a delay in fixing the fuel system failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The part to do the recall repair is not yet available
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
the dealer is unable to obtain the parts for the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure fuel pump can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the high-pressure fuel pump has failed and needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CP4 fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: metal shavings in the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DEF pump can cause the truck to shut down, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: metal shavings in the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to CP4 Fuel Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CP4 fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: the diesel exhaust fluid warning light illuminates
the engine stability control warning light illuminates
and the fuel system is destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Lack of Engine Oil
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of engine oil can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The oil pressure warning light illuminates
the oil consistency is like jelly
and the engine needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing safety recalls can leave vehicles on the road with potentially life-threatening defects, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle is on a waiting list for repair
and the dealer does not have the necessary parts to complete the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) Warning Light Illumination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the DEF warning light can indicate a problem with the emissions system, which can lead to decreased engine performance and potentially cause a loss of power.
symptoms: and the vehicle may experience decreased engine performance.
